Simple bash script to collect system details.

Creates two files by default:

/var/tmp/$HOSTNAME.$DATE.txt
and
/var/tmp/$HOSTNAME.$DATE.htm

I've been pushing this script down the road for a while, and it's come in very handy.

Distribute throughout your cluster and upload the resulting files.. Copy and paste the HTML into your favorite Wiki, or whatever.

Use the results to upload claims of falsified server capacity, gain insight into your server infrastructure, or justify a purchase request.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Example:

----------------------------
----------------------------
System Configuration report for box

Tue May  8 15:37:49 CDT 2012

----------------------------
----------------------------


Debian Linux version:

wheezy/sid



